<title>SINGAPORE: Saville sees US$50-100 mln Asia sales.</title>
<headline>Saville sees US$50-100 mln Asia sales.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-04-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>U.S. accounting software firm Saville Systems said on Thursday it expected its turnover in the Asia Pacific region to grow quickly over the next two or three years.</p>
<p>&quot;By 2000, we see US$50 million to US$100 million worth of revenue from the Asia Pacific region, or around 30 percent of forecast global turnover. Now it is negligible,&quot; Kiley said in an interview.</p>
<p>The company's global revenue in 1996 was $54 million.  </p>
<p>Saville sells advanced accounting computer programs that allow telecommunications companies to send out integrated bills to customers covering all the various services they use.</p>
<p>-- Singapore newsroom (65 8703199)</p>
